basic tenet of science is that it is testable.  

117
00:10:02,231 --> 00:10:07,269
The heart of the scientific method is that 
hypotheses can be tested with experiments. After  

118
00:10:07,269 --> 00:10:12,141
doing a number of experiments the results allow 
the calculation of a confidence in the conclusion  

119
00:10:12,141 --> 00:10:18,881
being true, and not just some random variation. A 
probability of 95% is normally the lowest accepted  

120
00:10:18,881 --> 00:10:23,852
in science. So, in other words, it's okay if 
one experiment in 20 gives a false result.

121
00:10:25,020 --> 00:10:30,559
In climate science the observation is that 
global temperature has been going up as  

122
00:10:30,559 --> 00:10:36,165
well as the level of CO2. The hypothesis 
is that CO2 released into the atmosphere  

123
00:10:36,165 --> 00:10:39,201
by human activity is causing 
the higher temperature.

124
00:10:40,169 --> 00:10:46,075
The problem is that it's not possible to design 
a repeatable experiment to test this hypothesis  

125
00:10:46,075 --> 00:10:51,747
because of the size, complexity, and uniqueness 
of the system. After all there's only one planet  

126
00:10:51,747 --> 00:10:58,787
earth and it's rather complicated. So we're 
left with conjectures and predictions. Applying  

127
00:10:58,787 --> 00:11:03,292
statistical models to the past temperature 
data can generate a prediction for the future,  

128
00:11:03,292 --> 00:11:08,063
but the confidence limits are so wide 
that the predictions are kind of useless.

129
00:11:08,797 --> 00:11:15,371
And this approach can't say whether CO2 is causing 
the change. So, the climate models that predict  

130
00:11:15,371 --> 00:11:20,542
a temperature response to CO2 have to be 
deterministic. That is, they have to assume that  

131
00:11:20,542 --> 00:11:26,715
the inputs will determine the temperature. So the 
assertion, based on these models, that CO2 causes  

132
00:11:26,715 --> 00:11:31,587
global warming is actually circular reasoning. 
And that's a that's a big no-no in science.

133
00:11:33,522 --> 00:11:39,995
The second point is that science cannot prove 
theories to be true only false. Observing a result  

134
00:11:41,430 --> 00:11:45,834
predicted by a hypothesis that doesn't prove the 
hypothesis as there may be other explanations.  

135
00:11:46,468 --> 00:11:52,541
So higher temperatures, for example, could be 
the result of something other than CO2. But  

136
00:11:52,541 --> 00:11:59,048
if the data shows higher temperatures with lower 
levels of CO2 that would disprove the hypothesis.

137
00:11:59,682 --> 00:12:06,221
Number three: correlation doesn't mean causation. 
So even if the CO2 levels and the temperatures are  

138
00:12:06,221 --> 00:12:13,195
